headlines.description: — Desmond Bane scored 21 points, Jaren Jackson Jr. had 19 and the Memphis Grizzlies rolled without All-Star Ja Morant, beating the Indiana Pacers 135-102 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grizzlies roll without Morant, beat Pacers 135-102

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving made it two nights in a row with a 60-point scorer in the NBA.
headlines.shortLinkText: Irving scores career-best 60 points, Nets rout Magic 150-108

headlines.description: — The game plan didn't call for Max Strus to play Tuesday night. He was not in the Miami Heat rotation to start the game, only entering after halftime because Jimmy Butler left with a sprained ankle.
headlines.shortLinkText: Strus leads late rally, Heat hold off Pistons 105-98

events.name: Phoenix Suns at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Devin Booker explained that his stirring and pivotal sequence of baskets against the New Orleans Pelicans was really just his way of following coaches' instructions on clock management at the end of quarters.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker scores 27 in 30 minutes, Suns sink Pelicans, 131-115
